{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "d3f2b1a0-5a4a-4a1a-9c0a-1a2b3c4d5e6f",
    "name": "PranataCRM API",
    "description": "Auth + Users + Contacts + Companies endpoints for PranataCRM.\n\nUse the \"PranataCRM Local\" environment alongside this collection. Auth cookies (access_token/refresh_token), the dev-mode X-Tenant-Slug header, and IDs produced along the way (tenant_id, user_id, contact_id, company_id) are captured and re-injected automatically by the collection's pre-request/test scripts — no manual copy-paste needed.\n\nSuggested run order: Register Tenant -> Login -> (everything else). Re-running \"Register Tenant\" always creates a brand-new tenant/user (unique slug/email per run), so the whole collection can be run repeatedly (including via Newman/CI) without 409 conflicts.\n\nTwo requests need one manual value because the backend has no endpoint to list them yet:\n- Create User / Invite User need `role_id` (a Role UUID). Look one up in the `roles` table for your tenant (the tenant's \"Administrator\" role is auto-created on registration) and set the `role_id` environment variable.\n- Accept Invite needs `invite_token` (the JWT emailed to the invitee). Paste it from the email/logs into the `invite_token` environment variable.\n\nSearch Users / Lookup Users and Search Companies / Lookup Companies are the autocomplete endpoints behind the owner_id and company_id pickers on the frontend — they return a lightweight summary shape (id + a couple of display fields), not the full resource.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-inject the dev-mode tenant slug header and auth cookies on every",
          "// request in this collection, so nothing needs to be copy-pasted by hand.",
          "const tenantSlug = pm.environment.get('tenant_slug');",
          "if (tenantSlug) {",
          "    pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Tenant-Slug', value: tenantSlug });",
          "}",
          "",
          "const accessToken = pm.environment.get('access_token');",
          "const refreshToken = pm.environment.get('refresh_token');",
          "const cookieParts = [];",
          "if (accessToken) cookieParts.push('access_token=' + accessToken);",
          "if (refreshToken) cookieParts.push('refresh_token=' + refreshToken);",
          "if (cookieParts.length) {",
          "    pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'Cookie', value: cookieParts.join('; ') });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Capture Set-Cookie (access_token/refresh_token) and X-Request-ID from",
          "// every response so later requests stay authenticated automatically and",
          "// failures are easy to correlate with a backend log line.",
          "const setCookieHeaders = pm.response.headers.all().filter(function (h) {",
          "    return h.key.toLowerCase() === 'set-cookie';",
          "});",
          "setCookieHeaders.forEach(function (h) {",
          "    const match = h.value.match(/^(access_token|refresh_token)=([^;]+)/);",
          "    if (match) {",
          "        pm.environment.set(match[1], match[2]);",
          "    }",
          "});",
          "",
          "const requestId = pm.response.headers.get('X-Request-ID');",
          "if (requestId) {",
          "    pm.environment.set('last_request_id', requestId);",
          "}",
          "",
          "pm.test('Status code is not 5xx (X-Request-ID: ' + requestId + ')', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.below(500);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000/api/v1"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
